  "prompt": "How much money did each candidate spend in the 1912 election?",
  "response": "In the 1912 U.S. presidential election, the major candidates and their campaign spending were as follows:\n\n1. **Woodrow Wilson (Democratic Party)**\n   - Wilson spent approximately $300,000 on his campaign.\n\n2. **Theodore Roosevelt (Progressive Party)**\n   - Roosevelt spent around $600,000 on his campaign.\n\n3. **William Howard Taft (Republican Party)**\n   - Taft's campaign expenditure was about $160,000.\n\n4. **Eugene V. Debs (Socialist Party)**\n   - Debs spent approximately $60,000 on his campaign.\n\nThese figures are adjusted for the time and represent the reported expenditures by each campaign. Note that campaign finance reporting was less stringent during this period, so actual numbers might vary slightly depending on the source.",
